    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "ruby",
      "data": "class Person\n  attr_reader :name\n\n  def initialize(name)\n    @name = name\n  end\nend\n\nperson1 = Person.new('James')\nperson1.name.reverse!\nputs person1.name"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "ruby",
      "data": "class Person\n  def initialize(name)\n    @name = name\n  end\n\n  def name\n    @name.clone\n  end\nend\n\nperson1 = Person.new('James')\nperson1.name.reverse!\nputs person1.name"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "data": "<p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px 0px 1.75rem; padding: 0px; font-family: myriad-pro, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; word-wrap: break-word; font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(251, 251, 251);\">In the initial example,&nbsp;<code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Monaco, 'Andale Mono', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; border: 0px solid rgb(62, 66, 69); padding: 0.1875rem 0.375rem; display: inline; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; text-shadow: none;\">@name</code>&nbsp;was modified through the invocation of a destructive method. This is because getter methods typically return a reference to the instance variable. If you use this reference to mutate the return value, you also mutate the instance variable.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-family: myriad-pro, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.75; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; word-wrap: break-word; font-variant-ligatures: normal; orphans: 2; widows: 2; background-color: rgb(251, 251, 251);\">To prevent this, we can invoke the&nbsp;<code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Monaco, 'Andale Mono', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; border: 0px solid rgb(62, 66, 69); padding: 0.1875rem 0.375rem; display: inline; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; text-shadow: none;\">#clone</code>&nbsp;method on&nbsp;<code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Monaco, 'Andale Mono', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; border: 0px solid rgb(62, 66, 69); padding: 0.1875rem 0.375rem; display: inline; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; text-shadow: none;\">@name</code>, which returns a copy of&nbsp;<code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Monaco, 'Andale Mono', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; border: 0px solid rgb(62, 66, 69); padding: 0.1875rem 0.375rem; display: inline; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; text-shadow: none;\">@name</code>&nbsp;instead of a reference to it. This means that any modifications done to the return value won't affect the value of&nbsp;<code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Monaco, 'Andale Mono', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; border: 0px solid rgb(62, 66, 69); padding: 0.1875rem 0.375rem; display: inline; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; text-shadow: none;\">@name</code>. Note that we should also remove the&nbsp;<code style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Consolas, Monaco, 'Andale Mono', 'Ubuntu Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8125rem; border: 0px solid rgb(62, 66, 69); padding: 0.1875rem 0.375rem; display: inline; border-top-left-radius: 0px; border-top-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-right-radius: 0px; border-bottom-left-radius: 0px; text-shadow: none;\">attr_reader</code>&nbsp;line since we are providing a customized getter method.</p>"
    }
  ]
